[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "The Python companion implements all nine pseudocode steps end-to-end with correct boto3 API calls: bedrock_runtime.invoke_model with proper body/modelId/guardrail kwargs, comprehend_medical.detect_entities_v2 with Text parameter, s3_client.put_object with Bucket/Key/Body/ContentType, and dynamodb Table put_item/update_item using ExpressionAttributeNames/Values. Adaptive retry Config is applied to all clients. Healthcare-specific considerations are extensively commented: no-PHI logging, byte-not-character limits for Comprehend Medical, SSE-KMS encryption, HIPAA retention, minimum-necessary scoping, Part 2 handling, Decimal-via-str for DynamoDB floats, and negation/uncertainty preservation. Error handling comments explain each try/except rationale (e.g., per-chunk LLM/CM failures are logged and tolerated so aggregation isn't blocked). The core recipe pattern—chunking, per-chunk extraction with LLM+Comprehend Medical cross-check, chronological aggregation, must-include checklist with backfill, grounded generation with provenance, validation with JSON-path resolution and token overlap, archive and deliver—is fully implemented with working logic, not placeholder bodies. The orchestration function runs the pipeline on synthetic sample data. Items explicitly flagged as 'stubbed' (authorization hook, EHR/PDF delivery endpoints, commented-out HealthLake/StepFunctions calls) are external integration points clearly documented as out-of-scope for an illustrative example, not missing implementations of the recipe pattern itself."}